http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Khadi-utsav-from-today/article13982946.ece

A month-long exhibition of khadi and village industries products is set to begin from Wednesday at Freedom Park. It is being organised by the Karnataka State Khadi and Village Industries Board. It has set up over 200 stalls to enable rural artisans to promote their products. Manufacturers will sell their products at a discount ranging from 25 per cent to 35 per cent.A variety of cultural programmes by artistes from different parts of the State and a fashion show have been arranged on public holidays. Visitors can expect live demonstrations on processing of certain products. Some freedom fighters will be felicitated.Minister for Small Industries Satish L. Jarkiholi will inaugurate the exhibition and Minister for Food, Civil Supplies and Consumers Affair Dinesh Gundu Rao will preside. Bengaluru Minister K. J. George will inaugurate the live demonstration. Revanna, MLC, will inaugurate the stalls.